                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the east wall of the central shrine in the Naṭanapādēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 44: 1113-14 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription records an undertaking given by the Śivabrāhmaṇa Tirunīlakaṇṭhaṉ and a number of others to Parā . . . . . taṉ Nalśuṅga[n*] tavi[r*]ttaśōla-ppal[la*]varaiyaṉ to burn a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp, in the temple of Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiya Mahādēva in Śōḻakulavallinallūr in Paṭṭāṉpākkai-nāḍu in Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu for 1 1/2 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> received. Śōḻappallavaraiyaṉ is said to have been in the enjoyment of a <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> in the temple.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
